I saw not only a cross marked on the sore- heads of all the AbiponeS, but likewise black crosses woven in the red woollen garments of many. Itis a very surprizing circumstance that they did this before they were acquainted with the religion of Christ, when the signification s and merits of the cross were unknown to them. Perhaps they learnt some veneration for the cross, or gained an idea of its possessing great virtues from their Spanish captives, or from those Abipones who had lived in captivity amongst the Spaniards,

The Abiponian women, not content with the marks common to both sexes, have their face, breast‚ and arms covered with black figures of various shapes, so that they present the appear- ance of a Turkish carpet.
